This utility allows the php manual to be browsed via the commandline
and hence from editors.

The cache is placed in .phpm

Installation
-----------
sudo apt-get install wget sed tidy xmlstarlet konwert

wget http://www.aaronsw.com/2002/html2text/html2text.py
wget http://www.shelldorado.de/scripts/cmds/urlencode.txt

Please these files (without extentions) and phpm in a dir reachable
by your $PATH

Make them executable.

Usage
-----
phpm <function>
phpm --clear clears the cache
phpm --short shows the method signature on a single line

Thanks to Troels Knak-Nielsen ((https://github.com/troelskn) for allowing me to place this up here.
Original: http://blogs.sitepoint.com/php-manual-cli-style-20/
